com.xekri.leakvm.sdk

Interface API.ApiConnectionCallback

  • Enclosing class:
    API

    public static interface API.ApiConnectionCallback
    The ApiConnectionCallback interface must be implemented by any callback whose instances are intended to receive a response over a connection thread. The class must define a methods called onDisconnected and onConnected.

    This interface is used by the method: setCallback.

    Since:
    1.0.0, 01/01/2017
    See Also:
    API

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onConnected(API api)
      When you use an object that implements the ApiConnectionCallback interface to create a connection callback, The thread returns a response called onConnected when the API connects.
      void onDisconnected(API api)
      When you use an object that implements the ApiConnectionCallback interface to create a connection callback, The thread returns a response called onDisconnected when the API disconnects.
      void onExecuteError(API api, java.lang.String methodName, java.lang.Exception error)
      When you use an object that implements the ApiConnectionCallback interface to create a connection callback, The thread returns a response called onExecuteError when the API has a execution error.
